<br>
With all of the tension that's been around recently (and hopefully seems to have disipated), I thought that I'd repeat some of the comments that were made in the officer's forums as we tried to keep each other calm (not always successfully) so we wouldn't add to the chaos.<br>
<br>
&quot;If it seems that somehow you are talking to a guildmate and you are both not managing to understand what the other is saying, give it up.<br>
smile, shrug, and just say hey, whatever lol, no worries, just not gonna get it for now. Some people react very defensively when questioned at all, let alone many times due to an unclear text explanation.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sarcasm, comedy, intent, thoughtfullness, empathy, sympathy.......list goes on. Anyway, those things DO NOT get translated well in written text. Mind you the #1 form of human communication is &quot;non-verbal&quot;. Written text is dam hard to communicate ideas and views.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;why do you guys think I so incesantly use text emotes? <br>
;o) 8o ) 8o / 8o ( I want to be sure to convey the emotion meant with what I am saying to prevent mis-understanding.&quot;<br>
<br>
-- Aya<br>
